id: pm-jozc
title: "MCP narrow tools silently drop top-level filter keys (pm_list {type:Task} returns unfiltered)"
description: "agent-UX audit F7: optionsWithAuthor reads only args.options, so the obvious agent shape pm_list {type:'Task'} returns ALL items (a stderr/warnings note is added but the result is wrong-sized). Hoist recognized filter keys (status/type/tag/priority/limit) from top-level into options. Complements [[pm-rmjy]]."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:mcp",never-block
created_at: "2026-06-07T17:04:17.730Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-08T06:26:03.609Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-5k4v
comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T19:58:21.572Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Execution kickoff: duplicate-check confirms this remains the canonical open MCP filter-hoisting bug. Implementing top-level args hoist for narrow MCP tools so pm_list/search filters are applied as expected."
  "2026-06-07T20:01:35.493Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Implemented first pass: pm_list/pm_search now accept declared top-level filter keys (status/type/tag/priority/limit, plus list offset/search mode) by hoisting them into options only when nested options do not already specify those keys. Also declared these keys in MCP tool schemas to avoid false unexpected-key warnings. Added integration coverage verifying applied filters and precedence of nested options over contradictory top-level keys. Targeted test passed (14/14)."
  "2026-06-07T20:47:41.050Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Contracts snapshot refreshed and current after MCP list/search schema top-level filter key additions (pnpm contracts:update + contracts:check)."
  "2026-06-07T21:31:56.420Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Verification evidence: manual temp-project MCP invocation against dist/mcp/server.js confirmed top-level pm_list filter keys (type/tag/limit) are applied and echoed in filters; targeted suite + full coverage pass."
  "2026-06-08T06:26:00.798Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,Merged in PR #147 (commit d05b21d529e3ed4f5734a029b98ed242fe8fb461). MCP pm_list/pm_search now hoist declared top-level filter keys into options while preserving nested options precedence; integration coverage added.
